data.title: Sweet Dog Experience, Kopecky Family Band lead stacked Tuscaloosa weekend (band calendar)
data.meta_description: Performing this weekend: Baak Gwai, Sweet Dog Experience, Kopecky Family Band, Mojo Trio, Great American Breakdown, Blackberry Smoke, CBDB and many more.
data.text:
-- Tuscaloosa music lovers will need to split their time wisely like they would at a festival on a stacked music weekend in town.

Saturday night might deliver the toughest choices of all, with Egan's hosting Crap Out 4 featuring Sweet Dog Experience, Ham Bagby, Blaine Duncan, GT and many more. On the other side of downtown, the Kopecky Family Band and Leagues and Early Americans will rock Green Bar.

Those and many other excellent choices stand out, so good luck with that.

Our recommendations are in

bold

.

BAMA THEATRE

Thursday: Jake Shimabukuro

EGAN'S

Friday: Baak Gwai, Sound & Shape, West Ghost

Saturday: Crap Out 4: Ham Bagby, Blaine Duncan, The Crown Imps, The F---ing Sea, GT, Jack Oblivian featuring The Sweet Dog Experience

GREEN BAR

Thursday: The Great American Breakdown, LF Knighton

Friday: IQ, DJ Shake

Saturday: Kopecky Family Band, Leagues and Early Americans
